I'm using perl v5.8.0 built for i386-linux-thread-multi

When I try running this script:

#!/usr/bin/perl -w
#
# prints XL file to standard output

use strict;
use DBI;
use Spreadsheet::WriteExcel::FromDB;

my $dbh = DBI->connect("dbi:mysql:rosedb", "roseadm", "jih1ying", {RaiseError=>1, PrintError=>0});
my $ss = Spreadsheet::WriteExcel::FromDB->read($dbh,"inventory");

print $ss->as_xls;
__END__

I get this error:

DBD::mysql::db selectall_arrayref failed: You have an error in your SQL syntax.  Check the manual that corresponds to your MySQL server version for the right syntax to use near 'FROM inventory' at line 1 at /usr/local/share/perl/5.8.0/Spreadsheet/WriteExcel/FromDB.pm line 134.

When I run this script:

#!/usr/bin/perl -w
#
# prints XL file to standard output

use strict;
use DBI;
use Spreadsheet::WriteExcel::Simple;

my $dbh = DBI->connect("dbi:mysql:rosedb", "roseadm", "jih1ying", {RaiseError=>1, PrintError=>0});

my $ss = Spreadsheet::WriteExcel::Simple->new;

$ss->write_row($_) foreach @{$dbh->selectall_arrayref("select * from inventory")};

print $ss->data;
__END__

I get the table contents as expected.
